label: Genève, Bibliothèque de Genève, Ms. lat. 33

metadata.label: Place of Origin (English)
metadata.value: Workshop located in the west of France, maybe in Nantes (France, Loire-Atlantique)

metadata.label: Summary (English)
metadata.value: This book of hours in the Parisian fashion is richly illuminated and was made for the diocese of Nantes in the third quarter of the 15th century. It was owned by the Petau family during the 17th century. In 1720 it was purchased by Ami Lullin of Geneva and donated to the Bibliothèque de Genève.

metadata.label: Persons
metadata.value: Former possessor: Lullin, Ami; Former possessor: Petau, Alexandre; Former possessor: Petau, Paul
